<font color="#FF0000">EDWARD'S COMBAT THREAD</font><br>
<tt>Mon Sep  1 20:57:52 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Edward, I think your desire is good, for a thread such as this for Combat Vets. Believe it on not, I did not double post, I didn't even single post.  Anyone can copy and paste, I guess.  I read this thread when it was just you alone, and decided to leave it to you and yours, to not post at all.<br><br>
I am sorry that someone is playing games with my posts. While I don't regret what I said (of course) I had no intention of posted it on this thread. I respect what you are trying to do, even if I don't think it can work.<br><br>
I respect all of you that were actual combat veterans, (surprise?). As I have said, a bad war does not mean that it was faught by bad men.  You guys, or most of you, were genuine hero's, and had it been a politically correct war, if such a oxymoron exists, you would have got that ticker tape parade you deserve. Maybe to many Tom Clancy novels, who knows.<br><br>
You went, you faught, you died, your bled.<br>
I resisted. I faught the &quot;war machine&quot;, I lived, although some students didn't (Kent State), and I didn't bleed. I served my country in a different manner. I did not run. To me I am still just as patriotic as any of you.  <br><br>
Richard, you who ran to Canada, get no solice from me. To me that was the easy way out. Too damn easy.  About as easy as the rich kids who dad's bought them a deferrment so the poor kids could fight instead, or by the minorities who were not able to hide in college.  I didn't hide and I didn't run, and I'll be damn, but I didn't double post on your thread either.<br><br>
I may drop by and read once in awhile, but I respect what you are trying to do.  I would do the same, but clearly I am outnumbered and even more clearly, out gunned.  (amen to that).  <br><br>
Who ever is doing the cut and paste number on me, thanks a lot.  I don't need your help. I am more than capable of eating crow, be it fried or baked, or screaming in the morning.  <br><br>
de doc
